"title": "4165: exorcism",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4165",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The expulsion of an evil spirit or spirits from a person. Jesus Christ has unique authority as an exorcist. He delegated this authority to the disciples.</p>\n<h2>Exorcism was practised with varying degrees of success by Jews and pagans</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:22\">MAT 7:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:27\">MAT 12:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:19\">LUK 11:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:13-Acts19:16\">ACT 19:13–19:16</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ had unique authority as an exorcist</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:27\">MRK 1:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:36\">LUK 4:36</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:25-Matt12:28\">MAT 12:25–12:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:17-Luke11:18\">LUK 11:17–11:18</a> <em>The authority Jesus Christ exercised over evil spirits demonstrated that God's kingly authority was present in him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:29\">MAT 12:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:27\">MRK 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:21-Luke11:22\">LUK 11:21–11:22</a> <em>Jesus Christ is the “strong man”. His power over evil spirits shows that Satan is defeated.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ had a general ministry of exorcism</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16\">MAT 8:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:34\">MRK 1:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:39\">MRK 1:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:17-Luke6:18\">LUK 6:17–6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:21\">LUK 7:21</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ gave the apostles power to cast out evil spirits</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1\">MAT 10:1</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:7\">MRK 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1\">LUK 9:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14-Mark3:15\">MRK 3:14–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:17\">MRK 16:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:17\">LUK 10:17</a></p>\n<h2>After the ascension the apostles cast out evil spirits</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:16\">ACT 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:12\">ACT 19:12</a></p>\n<h2>Various symptoms associated with the need for exorcism</h2>\n<h3>Violent or self-destructive behaviour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:1-Mark5:5\">MRK 5:1–5:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:27-Luke8:29\">LUK 8:27–8:29</a></p>\n<h3>Deafness and muteness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:32\">MAT 9:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:17\">MRK 9:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a></p>\n<h3>Seizures</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:14-Matt17:15\">MAT 17:14–17:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:17-Mark9:18\">MRK 9:17–9:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:38-Luke9:39\">LUK 9:38–9:39</a></p>\n<h2>Various components of exorcism</h2>\n<h3>A word of command</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:25\">MRK 1:25</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:35\">LUK 4:35</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:32\">MAT 8:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25\">MRK 9:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:18\">ACT 16:18</a></p>\n<h3>The demons recognise the source of the authority addressing them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:24\">MRK 1:24</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:34\">LUK 4:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:29\">MAT 8:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:7\">MRK 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:28\">LUK 8:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:17\">ACT 16:17</a></p>\n<h3>Exorcism was often accompanied by an element of violence or trauma</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:26\">MRK 1:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:26\">MRK 9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:32\">MAT 8:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:13\">MRK 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:32-Luke8:33\">LUK 8:32–8:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:16\">ACT 19:16</a></p>\n<h3>Exorcism changes the behaviour or condition of the person delivered</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:15\">MRK 5:15</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:35\">LUK 8:35</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33\">MAT 9:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a></p>\n<h3>An exorcised person may be ``repossessed''</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:43-Matt12:45\">MAT 12:43–12:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:24-Luke11:26\">LUK 11:24–11:26</a></p>\n<h2>Methods of exorcism other than the word of command</h2>\n<h3>Exorcism may be achieved at a distance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:21-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:21–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:24-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:24–7:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:12\">ACT 19:12</a></p>\n<h3>On rare occasions an object is used</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:12\">ACT 19:12</a> <em>This was an unusual demonstration of power in a city noted for magic.</em></p>\n<h3>David's music brought relief to Saul</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:14-1Sam16:16\">1SA 16:14–16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:23\">1SA 16:23</a></p>\n<h3>Intensive prayer is sometimes necessary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:29\">MRK 9:29</a></p>",
